               <p>THOMAS BLIZARD. I am a <rs id="t18331128-34-viclabel202" type="occupation">shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-34-victim455 t18331128-34-viclabel202"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18331128-34-crimeloc203">Holywell-street, Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-34-crimeloc203" type="placeName" value="Holywell-street, Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-34-crimeloc203" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-34-off200 t18331128-34-crimeloc203"></join>; between ten and eleven o'clock in the morning of the 9th of November, I was at my window at work; I saw a boy come up to my window, take a pair of shoes and run away with them - they were outside, but unless I put them out I should not sell them - I pursued the prisoner; the policeman took him - I lost sight of him, but I am sure he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-34-person456">
                  MATILDA 
                  HAWKINS
